org.mariuszgromada.math.entertain.janetsudoku

Class SudokuSolver

  • java.lang.Object
    • org.mariuszgromada.math.entertain.janetsudoku.SudokuSolver

  • public class SudokuSolver
extends java.lang.Object
    Sudoku board, with predefined Sudoku examples and possibility to load external examples from arrays or files. Class implements loading methods as well as Sudoku solving methods.
    Version:
    0.0.1
    Author:
    Mariusz Gromada
    mariusz.gromada@mathspace.pl

      • setCell

        public int setCell(int rowIndex,
                   int colIndex,
                   int digit)
        Manually set cell value.
        Parameters:
        rowIndex - Cell row index between 0 and 8.
        colIndex - Cell column index between 0 and 8.
        digit - Cell digit between 1 and 9, or EMPTY_CELL.
        Returns:
        Number of empty cells that left if cell definition correct, ERROR_SETCELL_INCORRECT_DEFINITION otherwise.

      • getCellDigit

        public int getCellDigit(int rowIndex,
                        int colIndex)
        Returns cell digit from current Sudoku board.
        Parameters:
        rowIndex - Cell row index between 0 and 8.
        colIndex - Cell column index between 0 and 8.
        Returns:
        Cell digit between 1 and 9, if cell empty then EMPTY_CELL. If indexes are out of range then error ERROR_GETCELLDIGIT_INCORRECT_INDEX is returned.

      • solve

        public int solve()
        Method starts solving procedure.
        Returns:
        if board state is BOARD_EMPTY then ERROR_SOLVE_SOLVING_NOT_STARTED, if board state is BOARD_ERROR then ERROR_SOLVE_SOLVING_NOT_STARTED, if board state is BOARD_LOADED then ERROR_SOLVE_SOLVING_NOT_STARTED, if board state is BOARD_READY then returns solving status: SUDOKU_SOLVED, ERROR_SOLVE_SOLVING_FAILED.

      • enableRndSeedOnEmptyCells

        public void enableRndSeedOnEmptyCells()
        By default random seed on empty cells is enabled. This parameter affects solving process only. Random seed on empty cells causes randomization on empty cells within empty cells with the same number of still free digits. Enabling extends ability to find different solutions, if exists.

      • disableRndSeedOnEmptyCells

        public void disableRndSeedOnEmptyCells()
        By default random seed on empty cells is enabled. This parameter affects solving process only. Random seed on empty cells causes randomization on empty cells within empty cells with the same number of still free digits. Disabling limits ability to find different solutions, if exists.

      • enableRndSeedOnFreeDigits

        public void enableRndSeedOnFreeDigits()
        By default random seed on free digits is enabled. This parameter affects solving process only. Random seed on free digits causes randomization on accessing free digits for a given empty cells. Each free digits is a starting point for a new recursive sub-path potentially leading to solution. Enabling extends ability to find different solutions, if exists.

      • disableRndSeedOnFreeDigits

        public void disableRndSeedOnFreeDigits()
        By default random seed on free digits is enabled. This parameter affects solving process only. Random seed on free digits causes randomization on accessing free digits for a given empty cells. Each free digits is a starting point for a new recursive sub-path potentially leading to solution. Disabling limits ability to find different solutions, if exists.
